ProScriptFunction.Description: Get Year from TrialMaster date
ProScriptFunction.Body: DECLARE @retVal nvarchar(4) BEGIN WITH tokens(p, a, b) AS ( SELECT 1, 1, charindex('/', @DataValue) UNION ALL SELECT p + 1, b + 1, charindex('/', @DataValue, b + 1) FROM tokens WHERE b > 0 ) SELECT @retVal = LTRIM(RTRIM(substring(@DataValue, a, CASE WHEN b > 0 THEN b-a ELSE 4000 END))) FROM tokens WHERE p = 1 END IF LEN(@retVal) = 4 AND ISNUMERIC(@retVal) = 1 RETURN @retVal RETURN null

ProScriptFunction.Description: Get Month from TrialMaster date
ProScriptFunction.Body: DECLARE @retVal nvarchar(2) BEGIN WITH tokens(p, a, b) AS ( SELECT 1, 1, charindex('/', @DataValue) UNION ALL SELECT p + 1, b + 1, charindex('/', @DataValue, b + 1) FROM tokens WHERE b > 0 ) SELECT @retVal = LTRIM(RTRIM(substring(@DataValue, a, CASE WHEN b > 0 THEN b-a ELSE 4000 END))) FROM tokens WHERE p = 2 END IF LEN(@retVal) BETWEEN 1 AND 2 AND ISNUMERIC(@retVal) = 1 BEGIN IF @retVal BETWEEN 1 AND 12 RETURN @retVal END RETURN null

ProScriptFunction.Description: Get Day from TrialMaster date

ProScriptFunction.Body: SET @Date = REPLACE(REPLACE(@Date, '---', '/NA/'),'-','/') -- if @date already in ISO format, replace dividers with stop words DECLARE @year nvarchar(4), @month nvarchar(2), nvarchar(10)) -- populate whe stop words are populated at the time of function generation INSERT INTO @StopWords(stopWord) VALUES ('UNK'),('NA') -- make sure there are two / characters in the date WHILE (LEN(@date)-LEN(REPLACE(@date,'/','')) < 2) SET @date = @date + '/' -- populate @DateAndTimeParts with date and time parts DECLARE @DXML AS XML = CAST(('' + REPLACE(@date, '/', '') + '') AS XML) INSERT INTO @DateAndTimeParts (IsStopWord, FixedValue) SELECT CASE WHEN N.value('.', 'VARCHAR(10)')='' THEN 1 WHEN s.stopWord IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, ISNULL(NULLIF(N.value('.', 'VARCHAR(10)'),''),(SELECT TOP 1 stopWord FROM @StopWords)) FROM @DXML.nodes('i') as T(N) LEFT OUTER JOIN @StopWords s ON s.stopWord = N.value('.', 'VARCHAR(10)') -- validate date parts: Replace invalid parts with empty('-') values UPDATE @DateAndTimeParts SET FixedValue = CASE WHEN (id = 1) AND (LEN(FixedValue) != 4 OR ISNUMERIC(FixedValue) != 1) THEN '-' --year WHEN (id = 2) AND (LEN(FixedValue) != 2 OR ISNUMERIC(FixedValue) != 1 OR FixedValue not between 1 and 12) THEN '-' --month WHEN (id = 3) AND (LEN(FixedValue) != 2 OR ISNUMERIC(FixedValue) != 1 OR FixedValue not between 1 and 31) THEN '-' --day ELSE FixedValue END -- the date is invalid in case one part is empty('-') and it's not a stop word IF(EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE FixedValue = '-' AND IsStopWord = 0)) GOTO INVALID_DATE -- delete trailing empty ('-') date and time values from @dateParts WHILE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE FixedValue = '-' AND id = (select max(id) from @DateAndTimeParts)) DELETE FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE FixedValue = '-' AND id = (select max(id) from @DateAndTimeParts) -- get day component SELECT @year = NULLIF(FixedValue,'-') FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE id = 1 SELECT @month = NULLIF(FixedValue,'-') FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE id = 2 SELECT @day = NULLIF(FixedValue,'-') FROM @DateAndTimeParts WHERE id = 3 -- validate day component if year, month and day present IF(@year IS NOT NULL AND @month IS NOT NULL AND @day IS NOT NULL) BEGIN IF(@day > DAY(DATEADD(month, ((@year - 1900) * 12) + @month, -1))) GOTO INVALID_DATE ELSE GOTO CONTINUE_PROC END -- validate day component month and day present and month is Feb. ELSE IF (@month='02') BEGIN IF (@day NOT BETWEEN 1 AND 29) GOTO INVALID_DATE ELSE GOTO CONTINUE_PROC END -- validate day component month and day present and month is not Feb. ELSE IF(@month IS NOT NULL and @day IS NOT NULL) BEGIN IF(@day > DAY(DATEADD(month, (1900 * 12) + @month, -1))) GOTO INVALID_DATE END CONTINUE_PROC: -- set datePart SELECT @datePart = COALESCE(@datePart + '-', '') + FixedValue FROM @DateAndTimeParts RETURN @datePart INVALID_DATE: RETURN NULL

ELSE IF (@month='02') BEGIN IF (@day NOT BETWEEN 1 AND 29) GOTO INVALID_DATE ELSE GOTO CONTINUE_PROC END -- validate day component month and day present and month is not Feb. ELSE IF(@month IS NOT NULL and @day IS NOT NULL) BEGIN IF(@day > DAY(DATEADD(month, (1900 * 12) + @month, -1))) GOTO INVALID_DATE END CONTINUE_PROC: -- set datePart SELECT @datePart = COALESCE(@datePart + '', '') + FixedValue FROM @DateAndTimeParts RETURN @datePart INVALID_DATE: RETURN NULL
